{"type":"message","id":"0f1b77e2","parentId":"63b0331c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:40:38.373Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8rcr47w5kfyp_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 153920\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiment (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. CFI Compression experiment done - showed CFI alone loses 92.9% recall\r\n3. Key finding: Constant Format Problem - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n4. Pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Need to run 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe observation from last pulse was \"No mutations applied this cycle\" - so I need to make a meaningful change.\r\n\r\nGiven the pending experiment is clearly the next step based on the synthesis, I should:\r\n1. Create a plan/experiment script for the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment\r\n2. Or actually run the experiment\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action advances the goals:\r\n- The experiment design is clear: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Need to run 200 pulses, 80/20 split\r\n- Compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to either:\r\n1. Create the experiment runner script\r\n2. Actually run the experiment on the pulse data\r\n\r\nGiven I'm in a \"pulse\" context and the pulse script calls the LLM, the most useful action is to create documentation or a script that will enable the next experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment plan for the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment that specifies exactly how to run it.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment revealed that constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0) are the primary failure mode. The next logical step is implementing and testing the hybrid scoring formula that should distinguish these from true research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the experiment specification and data processing script for Strategy C (Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring), implementing the formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0): score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (BUT capped at 1.0 means we need freq≥120)\r\n- Actually: score = 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 × 0.87 = 0.87\r\n- Reward research trajectory tokens (freq=80, CFI=0.8): score = 0.8 × 0.67 = 0.53\r\n- Penalize rare tokens (freq=3, CFI=0.6): score = 0.6 × 0.025 = 0.015\r\n\r\n## Problem Identified\r\nThe min(1, freq/120) caps at 1.0 for freq≥120, meaning constant-format tokens get score ≈ 0.87-1.0.\r\nThis DOES NOT distinguish them from research tokens (freq=136, CFI=0.96) → score = 0.96.\r\n\r\n## Revised Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) × [freq(T) < 150 ? 1 : 0]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis adds a hard cutoff at freq=150 to exclude constant-format tokens entirely.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Protocol\r\n1. Extract CFI and frequency for all tokens from pulse corpus\r\n2. Compute three scoring methods:\r\n   - A: CFI ≥ 0.5 (baseline)\r\n   - B: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND 3 ≤ freq < 120 (three-dimensional filter)\r\n   - C: score = CFI × min(1, freq/120) AND freq < 150 (hybrid)\r\n3. Evaluate on 200 pulses (160 train / 40 test)\r\n4. Metrics: precision, recall, F1 against human-identified research tokens\r\nfile: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:39:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381238371}}
